<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="69" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1027]" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,930,955]" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species honors Dr. John 
<taxonomicName box="[711,779,930,955]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Wahydra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curtis">Curtis</taxonomicName>
Callaghan, for his significant contribution to butterfly biodiversity, not only for his special contribution to the 
<taxonomicName box="[775,901,966,991]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Riodinidae</taxonomicName>
, but also to his collecting efforts of Neotropical 
<taxonomicName box="[151,289,1002,1027]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hesperiidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
